{
  "message": "test(polynomial): lock Hermite physicist / probabilist arithmetic parity\n\nAdded 15 goldens across 10 Hermite-family ops (hermadd/hermsub/hermmul/\nhermdiv/hermval and the probabilist hermeadd/hermesub/hermemul/hermediv/\nhermeval), each of which had a single fixture.\n\nPhysicist Hermite (H_n):\n- hermadd: equal-length, short+long padding\n- hermsub: equal-length, long-minus-short tail\n- hermmul: scalar\u00d7vector scaling, (H0+H1)\u00b2 = 3+2x+x\u00b2 via recurrence\n- hermdiv: textbook 4-term \u00f7 2-term with quotient/remainder\n  [-7.25, 0.5, 2.0] / [6.25]\n- hermval: H2(\u00b11,0) = [2,-2,2], full series at 0.5 \u2192 -1.0\n\nProbabilist Hermite (He_n):\n- hermeadd: equal-length\n- hermesub: long-minus-short tail\n- hermemul: (He0+He1)\u00b2 = 2+2x+x\u00b2 (differs from physicist by scale 2)\n- hermediv: quotient [-3.25, 0.5, 2.0] / remainder [3.25]\n  (half the physicist magnitude)\n- hermeval: He2(\u00b11,0) = [0,-1,0], full series at 0.5 \u2192 -0.5\n\n146 polynomial_differential cases total (from 131).\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>",
